name: The Kroya Panorama Points
address: 6GWQ+QJ, Batukandik, Nusa Penida, Klungkung Regency, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: While the place served as a brief stop for me, the island offers much better views elsewhere. There's a small shop where you can purchase some essentials, but it might not be worth spending an extended period of time there. Consider exploring other spots on the island for more captivating vistas and experiences.
review 2: Is not worthy go so far for that absolutely normal views
review 3: You have a good view but not really panoramic. Still pretty tho
review 4: the scenery is very beautiful, the air is also cool, just a very memorable experience for me
review 5: The view of the village is very good and also beautiful

name: Kimanis Sunset Point
address: Unnamed Road, 6GRQ+X8Q, Batukandik, Kec. Nusa Penida, Kabupaten Klungkung, Bali 80771, Indonesia
review 1: Warm welcome by Mr. Chris P. Bacon!
review 2: Good spot for sunset, accessible via narrow way up to the hill top.
review 3: The best place for enjoying sunset

name: Warung The Kroya Panorama Points
address: Batukandik, Nusa Penida, Klungkung Regency, Bali 80771, Indonesia
review 1:
The Nasi Goreng was pretty good, she makes it with less oil, so it is more healthy than the same dish made by most restaurants in Nusa Penida.
Also the prices are really friendly, 55k RP for 1 Nasi Goreng and an ice tea. No tax or service fee is added, you see the final price on the menu.
review 2: Great food and flavor and yes it was also SPICY!
review 3: We stopped here to break up the drive while doing a big lap around the island. It was breezy, there were views, the local food and fruit were excellent for refueling, and the lady that was working there was one of the nicest individuals we met on the island. The cute little chickens running around were a bonus!
review 4: amazing food & view and nice people :)
review 5: Passed this while driving around the island today, for some reason we stopped and said we needed to go back and try it. It didnâ€™t disappoint, such tasty food, amazingly friendly service and so cheap too!

name: Warung reva
address: 6GVM+6GV, Batukandik, Nusa Penida, Klungkung Regency, Bali 80771, Indonesia
review 1:
Great family business, , I was mind blown when they told me they own every shop in town as well as a tour agency.
This can really be you one stop place for everything.
